cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves adapting an unsupervised parser to learn from partial dependencies. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because the parser uses neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because the Graph Fragment Language used to express partial dependencies is similar to the graph structures used in computer vision.
